INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (5,'bg-img5f6b5fa64a4940wph160087235821440268.jpg','bg-img5f6b5fa69f58e7esb160087235807522900.jpg','bg-img5f6b5fa6c91835gxj160087235844927771.jpg',1600872359,1600873004,'promotion-de-l-investissement-l-api-se-rapproche-des-banques','promotion-of-investment-the-api-gets-close-of-banks','Promotion de l’investissement : l’API se rapproche des banques','Promotion of investment: the API gets closer to banks','Considérées comme des acteurs importants dans le développement de l’investissement, les banques congolaises sont appelées à jouer un  rôle décisif en finançant les activités économiques. Afin d’atteindre cet objectif, l’Agence pour la promotion des investissements (API) a organisé, le 23 avril, une réunion de concertation avec ces institutions financières opérant au Congo.','Considered as important actors in the development of investment, Congolese banks are called upon to play a decisive role in financing economic activities. In order to achieve this objective, the Investment Promotion Agency (API) organized a consultation meeting on April 23 with these financial institutions operating in Congo.','<p>L&rsquo;objectif vis&eacute; par cette rencontre dirig&eacute;e par la directrice g&eacute;n&eacute;rale de l&rsquo;API, Patricia Annick Mongo, est de cr&eacute;er un cadre de concertation et de r&eacute;flexion permanent et permettant &agrave; cette institution publique d&rsquo;&eacute;changer continuellement avec les banques sur la probl&eacute;matique de l&rsquo;investissement au Congo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cette rencontre a permis donc aux onze banques pr&eacute;sentes &agrave; ce rendez-vous et &agrave; l&rsquo;API d&rsquo;approfondir des r&eacute;flexions sur l&rsquo;ensemble des questions qui freinent vraisemblablement l&rsquo;investissement priv&eacute; au Congo, du point de vue des banques.</p>\r\n','<p>The objective of this meeting led by the Director General of the API, Patricia Annick Mongo, is to create a framework for consultation and permanent reflection and allowing this public institution to continuously discuss with the banks on the issue of l investment in Congo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This meeting therefore enabled the eleven banks present at this meeting and the API to deepen their thoughts on all the issues that are likely to hamper private investment in Congo, from the point of view of the banks.</p>\r\n',1),(6,'bg-img5f6b61b867b8a9nvz160087288815904916.jpg','bg-img5f6b61b8bbe456biy160087288862269999.jpg','bg-img5f6b61b8d937a1rpr160087288891677914.jpg',1600872889,1600938845,'lancement-d-un-nouveau-produit-pack-destinee-a-la-clientele-de-lcb-bank','launch-of-a-new-pack-product-intended-for-lcb-bank-customers','Lancement d\'un nouveau produit pack destinée à la clientèle de LCB Bank','Launch of a new pack product intended for LCB Bank customers','Le lundi  10 Octobre 2016, a eu lieu la mise en production officielle du produit PACK LCB BANK C’est une offre globale et forfaitaire destinée aux clients particuliers leur permettant de bénéficier d’avantages tarifaires sur un ensemble de produits et services de la LCB BANK.','On Monday, October 10, 2016, the official launch of the PACK LCB BANK product took place, which is a global and flat-rate offer intended for individual customers, allowing them to benefit from tariff advantages on a set of LCB BANK products and services.','<p>A cet effet trois types de PACK ont &eacute;t&eacute; cr&eacute;es pour &nbsp;r&eacute;pondre au besoin de notre client&egrave;le,notamment:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PACK FONCTIONNAIRE: C&rsquo;est une offre globale et forfaitaire destin&eacute;e aux salari&eacute;es du secteur public leur permettant de b&eacute;n&eacute;ficier d&rsquo;avantages tarifaires sur un ensemble de produits et services de la LCB BANK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PACK SALARIE PRIVE: C&rsquo;est une offre globale et forfaitaire destin&eacute;e aux salari&eacute;es priv&eacute;es leur permettant de b&eacute;n&eacute;ficier d&rsquo;avantages tarifaires sur un ensemble de produits et services de la LCB BANK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PACK ELITE: C&rsquo;est une offre globale et forfaitaire destin&eacute;e aux clients ELITE leur permettant de b&eacute;n&eacute;ficier d&rsquo;avantages tarifaires sur un ensemble de produits et services de la LCB BANK.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p>To this end, three types of PACK have been created to meet the needs of our customers, in particular:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>OFFICIAL PACK: This is a global and flat-rate offer intended for public sector employees, allowing them to benefit from tariff advantages on a set of products and services of LCB BANK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PRIVATE EMPLOYEE PACK: This is a global and flat-rate offer intended for private employees allowing them to benefit from tariff advantages on a set of products and services from LCB BANK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ELITE PACK: This is a global and flat-rate offer intended for ELITE customers, allowing them to benefit from tariff advantages on a set of products and services from LCB BANK.</p>\r\n',1),(7,'bg-img5f6b632c9c3f29nwq160087326061061214.jpg','bg-img5f6b632ef26885tdk160087326220119430.jpg','bg-img5f6b63307d45e2ozm160087326479396769.jpg',1600873267,NULL,'rencontre-du-directeur-general-de-lcb-bank-avec-le-ministre-de-la-culture-et-des-arts','meeting-of-the-managing-director-of-lcb-bank-with-the-minister-of-culture-and-arts','Rencontre du Directeur Général de LCB BANK avec le Ministre de la Culture et des Arts','Meeting of the Managing Director of LCB BANK with the Minister of Culture and Arts','MOHAMED Tahri, Directeur Général de la LCB Bank, a été l’hôte du ministre de la culture et des arts, Léonidas Carel MOTTOM MAMONA , mercredi 29 juin 2016 dans son cabinet de travail, à Brazzaville.','MOHAMED Tahri, Managing Director of LCB Bank, hosted the Minister of Culture and the Arts, Léonidas Carel MOTTOM MAMONA, on Wednesday June 29, 2016 in his office in Brazzaville.','<p>L&rsquo;entretient entre les deux personnalit&eacute;s s&rsquo;est focalis&eacute; sur les questions relatives &agrave; la culture et notamment au statut social des artistes et &agrave; l&rsquo;essor de la culture congolaise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outre les questions, les deux personnalit&eacute;s ont aussi abord&eacute; la question du FESPAM (Festival. Panafricain de musique), un &eacute;v&eacute;nement multisectoriel qui se d&eacute;roule apr&egrave;s deux ans, &agrave; Brazzaville. Le repr&eacute;sentant de la LCB Bank a par ailleurs, annonc&eacute;, que la Banque &agrave; travers sa fondation LCB Bank peut accompagner le ministre de la culture dans la construction ou l&rsquo;&eacute;quipement des biblioth&egrave;ques au niveau des h&ocirc;pitaux et des prisons.</p>\r\n','<p>The meeting between the two personalities focused on issues relating to culture and in particular the social status of artists and the development of Congolese culture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to questions, the two personalities also addressed the issue of FESPAM (Pan-African Music Festival), a multisectoral event that takes place after two years, in Brazzaville. The representative of LCB Bank also announced that the Bank, through its LCB Bank foundation, can support the Minister of Culture in building or equipping libraries in hospitals and prisons.</p>\r\n',1),(8,'bg-img5f6b66966a81f7ngp160087413448382902.jpg','bg-img5f6b66970e6362jyv160087413567694976.jpg','bg-img5f6b66977daed1sdm160087413515560486.jpg',1600874136,NULL,'lcb-bank-academy','lcb-bank-academy','LCB Bank Academy','LCB Bank Academy','Dans le cadre de son projet de rénovation et d’extension de son réseau d’agences, LCB Bank vient de se doter d’un immeuble R+4 abritant actuellement l’agence LCB Bank de Ouenzé, mais surtout LCB Bank Académie.','As part of its project to renovate and extend its branch network, LCB Bank has just acquired an R + 4 building currently housing the LCB Bank branch in Ouenzé, but above all LCB Bank Académie.','<p>LCB Bank Acad&eacute;mie ambitionne d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre un grand centre de formation, d&rsquo;abord pour le personnel interne&nbsp;<strong>LCB Bank</strong>&nbsp;notamment dans le cadre de leurs formations et dans des secteurs vari&eacute;s. LCB Acad&eacute;mie se veut &ecirc;tre une v&eacute;ritable plate-forme, un espace d&eacute;dier aussi au public externe, travailleurs, &eacute;tudiants, chercheurs d&rsquo;emploi, promoteurs de projet&hellip; donc un vrai environnement d&rsquo;incubation au centre duquel seront organiser des ateliers de r&eacute;flexion, &eacute;changes, partages, pr&eacute;sentation de projet sur plusieurs th&eacute;matique ayant trait &agrave; la recherche dans plusieurs secteurs de d&eacute;veloppement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCB Academy a &eacute;t&eacute; honor&eacute; par la visite de M.&nbsp;<strong>Brahim Benjelloun Touimi</strong>, l&rsquo;Administrateur Directeur g&eacute;n&eacute;ral de la BMCE Bank Of Africa ; ce dernier a rencontr&eacute; le Pr&eacute;sident de la R&eacute;publique du Congo le 05 f&eacute;vrier dernier, &agrave; l&rsquo;issue de son audience il a mentionn&eacute; ceci &laquo; Nous avons inform&eacute; le pr&eacute;sident de la R&eacute;publique des projets que nous envisageons pour la LCB Bank, notamment dans le domaine de mobile Banking et de la formation puisque LCB Bank cr&eacute;e sa propre Academy. &raquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dans sa vision d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre leader sur le march&eacute; bancaire congolais, LCB Bank a investi sur la formation de son capital humain, notamment dans l&rsquo;organisation avec l&rsquo;appui de la BMCE ACADEMY des formations tels que&nbsp;<strong>MBONGWANA</strong>&nbsp;(qui veut dire changement) destin&eacute; aux managers de la banque, et&nbsp;<strong>BONGUISSA</strong>&nbsp;qui veut dire (am&eacute;liorer), formation qui vise l&rsquo;am&eacute;lioration des pratiques commerciales avec comme publics concern&eacute;s : caissiers, agents d&rsquo;accueil, conseillers client&egrave;les&hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dans l&rsquo;attente du lancement de LCB Academy plusieurs formations ont eu lieu &agrave; savoir :</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sensibilisation sur les risques op&eacute;rationnels</li>\r\n	<li>Formation fiche cr&eacute;dit achat tv Startimes via LCB Bank</li>\r\n	<li>D&eacute;briefing MBONGWANA</li>\r\n	<li>Ateliers sur la Mon&eacute;tique (MAGIX)</li>\r\n	<li>Conf&eacute;rence d&eacute;bat Charte Manag&eacute;riale LCB Bank</li>\r\n	<li>Guichetier payeur et la probl&eacute;matique de l&rsquo;argent sale</li>\r\n	<li>Conflit d&rsquo;int&eacute;r&ecirc;ts : qu&rsquo;est-ce- que c&rsquo;est ?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n','<p>LCB Bank Acad&eacute;mie aims to be a large training center, first for internal LCB Bank staff, particularly in the context of their training and in various sectors. LCB Acad&eacute;mie aims to be a real platform, a space also dedicated to the external public, workers, students, job seekers, project promoters ... therefore a real incubation environment at the center of which will be organizing workshops for reflection, exchanges , sharing, presentation of project on several themes relating to research in several development sectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCB Academy was honored by the visit of Mr. Brahim Benjelloun Touimi, Managing Director of BMCE Bank Of Africa; the latter met the President of the Republic of Congo on February 5, at the end of his audience he mentioned the following: &quot;We have informed the President of the Republic of the projects that we are considering for LCB Bank, in particular in the field mobile banking and training since LCB Bank is creating its own Academy. &quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In its vision of being a leader in the Congolese banking market, LCB Bank has invested in the training of its human capital, in particular in the organization with the support of BMCE ACADEMY of trainings such as MBONGWANA (which means change) intended to the managers of the bank, and BONGUISSA which means (improve), training aimed at improving commercial practices with the target groups concerned: cashiers, reception agents, customer advisers, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While awaiting the launch of LCB Academy, several training courses took place, namely:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Awareness of operational risks</li>\r\n	<li>Startimes tv purchase credit card training via LCB Bank</li>\r\n	<li>Debriefing MBONGWANA</li>\r\n	<li>Workshops on Monetics (MAGIX)</li>\r\n	<li>Conference debate Management Charter LCB Bank</li>\r\n	<li>Paying teller and the problem of dirty money</li>\r\n	<li>Conflict of interest: what is it?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1),(9,'bg-img5f6b6ca0670a48nqc160087568081647900.jpg','bg-img5f6b6ca0c83e58otk160087568007689474.jpg','bg-img5f6b6ca11a5a27hrp160087568198777965.jpg',1600875681,NULL,'decoration-de-la-direction-generale','decoration-of-the-general-management','Décoration de la Direction Générale','Decoration of the General Management','Monsieur Mohamed Essaid BENJELLOUN TOUIMI & Monsieur Rachid RAISSI (Directeur Général Adjoint de LCB Bank), ont été élevés au grade de << Chevalier dans l’ordre du Mérite Congolais >> par le chef de l’Etat Congolais son Excellence Mr Denis SASSOU N’GUESSO, Grand Maitre des Ordres Nationaux.','Mr. Mohamed Essaid BENJELLOUN TOUIMI & Mr. Rachid RAISSI (Deputy Managing Director of LCB Bank), were elevated to the rank of \"Knight in the Congolese Order of Merit\" by the Congolese Head of State His Excellency Mr. Denis SASSOU N \'GUESSO, Grand Master of National Orders.','<p>Des d&eacute;corations qui confortent aussi le positionnement de banque dans le paysage bancaire congolais que son image d&rsquo;&eacute;tablissement bancaire s&eacute;rieux se voulant proche de ces clients, en satisfaisant leurs besoins en produits bancaires.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exprimant sa gratitude au Chef de l&rsquo;Etat pour cette marque d&rsquo;honneur et de distinction,&nbsp;<strong>Mohamed BENJELLOUN TOUIMI</strong>&nbsp;apr&egrave;s r&eacute;ception de l&rsquo;insigne a d&eacute;clar&eacute; :&nbsp;<strong>&lt;&gt;</strong>&nbsp;Cette distinction a-t-il poursuivi, est aussi une fa&ccedil;on de rendre hommage particulier au Groupe BMCE Bank Of Africa, &agrave; ses diff&eacute;rents pr&eacute;d&eacute;cesseurs ainsi que &agrave; l&rsquo;ensemble du personnel qui ont b&acirc;ti la grande maison de LCB Bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monsieur Rachid RAISSI pour sa part, a &eacute;t&eacute; d&eacute;cor&eacute; le m&ecirc;me jour que le Pr&eacute;sident Directeur G&eacute;n&eacute;rale de Eco O&iuml;l Energie le 04 mai 2018, remerciant &agrave; son tour le pr&eacute;sident de la R&eacute;publique du Congo, a soutenu que cette cons&eacute;cration est le fruit d&rsquo;un travail collectif. Aussi, a-t-il dit toute sa profonde reconnaissance &agrave; ses collaborateurs pour leur soutien, en saluant les efforts que d&eacute;ploie LCB Bank pour parmi les leaders pour sur le march&eacute; bancaire congolais.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parlant de la strat&eacute;gie nationale de d&eacute;ploiement de LCB Bank, rachi RAISSI a pr&eacute;cis&eacute; quelle suit la logique du d&eacute;veloppement &eacute;conomique du Congo. LCB Bank a-t-il fait savoir est pr&eacute;sente &agrave; Brazzaville, Pointe-Noire, Ouesso, Oyo, N&rsquo;kayi et Ngomb&eacute;. Son ambition, a-t-il expliqu&eacute;, est d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre plus proche de ses clients. Eclairant les journalistes sur le leadership de son &eacute;tablissement bancaire, il a indiqu&eacute; que LCB Bank b&eacute;n&eacute;ficie de l&rsquo;audience internationale du Groupe BMCE Bank Of Africa pr&eacute;sent dans quatre continents (Afrique, Am&eacute;rique, Asie, Europe).</p>\r\n','<p>Decorations which also reinforce the bank&#39;s positioning in the Congolese banking landscape and its image as a serious banking establishment wishing to be close to these customers, by satisfying their needs for banking products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Expressing his gratitude to the Head of State for this mark of honor and distinction, Mohamed BENJELLOUN TOUIMI after receiving the badge declared: &lt;&gt; This distinction, he continued, is also a way of paying particular tribute to the BMCE Bank Of Africa Group, to its various predecessors as well as to all the staff who built the big house of LCB Bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr. Rachid RAISSI for his part, was decorated on the same day as the CEO of Eco O&iuml;l Energie on May 4, 2018, thanking in turn the President of the Republic of Congo, maintained that this consecration is the result of a collective work. Also, he said his deep gratitude to his staff for their support, welcoming the efforts that LCB Bank is making for among the leaders in the Congolese banking market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Speaking of the national strategy of deployment of LCB Bank, rachi RAISSI specified which follows the logic of the economic development of Congo. LCB Bank, he said, is present in Brazzaville, Pointe-Noire, Ouesso, Oyo, N&rsquo;kayi and Ngomb&eacute;. His ambition, he explained, is to be closer to his customers. Enlightening journalists on the leadership of his banking establishment, he indicated that LCB Bank benefits from the international audience of the BMCE Bank Of Africa Group present in four continents (Africa, America, Asia, Europe).</p>\r\n',1),(10,'bg-img5f6cc3b39655d0amf160096350738662190.jpg','bg-img5f6cc3b3b34583woy160096350760639186.jpg','bg-img5f6cc3b3bc6f80vib160096350720704198.jpg',1600963508,NULL,'l-administrateur-directeur-generale-de-la-bmce-rencontre-le-chef-de-l-etat','bmce-managing-director-meets-with-head-of-state','L’Administrateur Directeur Générale de la BMCE rencontre le Chef de l’Etat','BMCE Managing Director meets with Head of State','Actionnaire principal de LCB Bank, la Banque Marocaine du Commerce Extérieur (BMCE) envisage de lancer de nouveaux produits bancaires au niveau de LCB Bank. Mr Brahim Benjelloun Touimi, a fait cette annonce le 5 février 2018 à Brazzaville, à l’issue de son audience avec le Président Denis Sassou N’Guesso.','Main shareholder of LCB Bank, the Moroccan Foreign Trade Bank (BMCE) plans to launch new banking products at LCB Bank level. Mr. Brahim Benjelloun Touimi, made the announcement on February 5, 2018 in Brazzaville, after his audience with President Denis Sassou N’Guesso.','<p>Nous avons inform&eacute; le pr&eacute;sident de la R&eacute;publique des projets que nous envisageons pour LCB Bank, notamment dans le domaine de mobile Banking et de la formation puisque LCB Bank cr&eacute;e sa propre Academy. &laquo; Nous souhaitons que LCB Bank puisse &ecirc;tre une banque enracin&eacute;e au Congo, en m&ecirc;me temps qu&rsquo;elle appartient &agrave; une communaut&eacute; plus large, panafricaine, &eacute;tant donn&eacute; que le groupe BMCE Bank of Africa est consid&eacute;r&eacute; par le&nbsp;<strong>Fonds Mon&eacute;taire International (FMI)&nbsp;</strong>comme l&rsquo;un des sept grands groupes panafricains &raquo;, a-t-il d&eacute;clar&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La R&eacute;publique du Congo, &agrave; l&rsquo;instar d&rsquo;autres pays p&eacute;troliers d&rsquo;Afrique centrale, conna&icirc;t une conjoncture &eacute;conomique difficile, marqu&eacute;e notamment par l&rsquo;abaissement des recettes budg&eacute;taires. Dans ce climat de r&eacute;cession, le Congo peut compter sur ses partenaires parmi lesquels la BMCE.<br />\r\n&laquo; Nous avons r&eacute;affirm&eacute; l&rsquo;appui apport&eacute; par un actionnaire et gestionnaire d&rsquo;une banque majeure dans le paysage congolais, r&eacute;affirm&eacute; notre soutien et notre engagement de continuer d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre pr&eacute;sent, en tant qu&rsquo;acteur et de mobiliser les ressources humaines et le savoir- faire, en intime collaboration avec nos partenaires congolais dont l&rsquo;Etat, dans l&rsquo;int&eacute;r&ecirc;t de l&rsquo;inclusion financi&egrave;re au Congo &raquo;, a indiqu&eacute; l&rsquo;administrateur de la BMCE. Selon notre Administrateur Directeur G&eacute;n&eacute;ral, LCB Bank a connu une p&eacute;riode de &laquo; croissance int&eacute;ressante &raquo;, estimant que c&rsquo;est en temps de crise &laquo; qu&rsquo;on doit compter sur les amis et aussi sur ceux qui se consid&egrave;rent comme Africains, Congolais de c&oelig;ur &raquo;. LCB Bank pr&eacute;voit d&rsquo;&eacute;tendre ses actions afin de contribuer &agrave; l&rsquo;int&eacute;gration du secteur informel national &agrave; travers, entre autres, la mise en place d&rsquo;une nouvelle gamme de produits de monnaie Electronique.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apr&egrave;s ce moment d&rsquo;&eacute;changes avec le Pr&eacute;sident de la r&eacute;publique, Mr Brahim BENJELLOUN a visit&eacute; LCB Bank Academy et a proc&eacute;d&eacute; &agrave; une s&eacute;ance de travail avec les managers de LCB Bank</p>\r\n','<p>We informed the President of the Republic of the projects that we are considering for LCB Bank, particularly in the field of mobile banking and training since LCB Bank is creating its own Academy. &quot;We want LCB Bank to be a bank rooted in Congo, at the same time as it belongs to a larger, pan-African community, given that the BMCE Bank of Africa group is considered by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) as the &#39;one of the seven major Pan-African groups,&#39; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Republic of Congo, like other oil-producing countries in Central Africa, is experiencing difficult economic conditions, marked in particular by lower budgetary revenues. In this climate of recession, the Congo can count on its partners, including BMCE.<br />\r\n&quot;We reaffirmed the support provided by a shareholder and manager of a major bank in the Congolese landscape, reaffirmed our support and our commitment to continue to be present, as an actor and to mobilize human resources and knowledge - to do, in close collaboration with our Congolese partners including the State, in the interest of financial inclusion in Congo &rdquo;, indicated the administrator of BMCE. According to our Managing Director, LCB Bank has experienced a period of &quot;interesting growth&quot;, believing that it is in times of crisis &quot;that we must rely on friends and also on those who consider themselves Africans, Congolese at heart&quot; . LCB Bank plans to expand its actions in order to contribute to the integration of the national informal sector through, among other things, the establishment of a new range of Electronic money products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After this moment of discussions with the President of the Republic, Mr. Brahim BENJELLOUN visited LCB Bank Academy and proceeded to a working session with the managers of LCB Bank</p>\r\n',1),(11,'bg-img5f6cc4c78e44e1tkv160096378339502265.jpg','bg-img5f6cc4c7ec5001qkl160096378369182864.jpg','bg-img5f6cc4c838e050hah160096378432500405.jpg',1600963785,NULL,'dispositif-de-formation-bonguissa','bonguissa-training-device','Dispositif de formation BONGUISSA','BONGUISSA training device','Les agents LCB Bank portent notre ambition commune d’impulser et d’incarner le changement au sein de notre banque. C’est dans ce cadre que le 28 mai 2018, ils se sont retrouvés dans le magnifique cadre de LCB Bank Academy, dans la phase pilote (avant la phase de déploiement sur l’ensemble du réseau LCB Bank) pour la poursuite du dispositif d’amélioration des pratiques commerciales des équipes commerciales de LCB Bank.','LCB Bank agents carry our common ambition to drive and embody change within our bank. It is in this context that on May 28, 2018, they met in the magnificent setting of LCB Bank Academy, in the pilot phase (before the deployment phase on the entire LCB Bank network) for the continuation of the system of \'improvement of the commercial practices of LCB Bank\'s commercial teams.','<p>Ce programme s&rsquo;inscrit dans une dynamique engag&eacute;e par notre banque visant la transformation &agrave; la fois du capital mat&eacute;riel et humain sur la place financi&egrave;re de la R&eacute;publique du Congo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cette formation a fait suite comme nous le savons, &agrave; la d&eacute;marche tr&egrave;s participative, ayant impliqu&eacute; les acteurs du r&eacute;seau des Agences de notre banque, dans une s&eacute;rie des ateliers qui ont permis de dresser un &eacute;tat des lieux de nos vieilles pratiques commerciales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ce processus avait laiss&eacute; transparaitre un certain nombre de constats, qui ont constitu&eacute;s la feuille de route du dispositif d&rsquo;am&eacute;lioration des pratiques commerciales, que les &eacute;quipes qui ont pris part aux diff&eacute;rents ateliers avaient appel&eacute; &laquo; BONGUISSA &raquo;.<br />\r\nNotre ambition commune &agrave; travers &laquo; BONGUISSA &raquo; a consist&eacute; &agrave; am&eacute;liorer ce que nous sommes, notre mani&egrave;re de faire, de parler, d&rsquo;accueillir et de servir notre client&egrave;le ; c&rsquo;est pourquoi cette formation s&rsquo;est faite pr&eacute;c&eacute;der par le programme &laquo; MBONGWANA &raquo;, lanc&eacute; depuis Novembre 2016, comme dispositif d&rsquo;accompagnement et de renforcement des capacit&eacute;s des managers de notre banque.<br />\r\nEn tant qu&rsquo;employ&eacute; de LCB Bank, nous sommes conscients des enjeux de l&rsquo;heure, et voulons mieux faire, changer et continuer &agrave; servir au mieux notre client&egrave;le et la fid&eacute;liser, mais aussi consolider davantage nos liens avec elle.<br />\r\nCe que nous souhaitons tous et qui demeure aujourd&rsquo;hui au centre de nos pr&eacute;occupations, c&rsquo;est de donner &agrave; notre client&egrave;le les raisons de continuer &agrave; nous renouveler sa confiance. Un v&eacute;ritable d&eacute;fi dira-t-on ! Mais nous y parviendront avec le m&ecirc;me &eacute;lan de d&eacute;termination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Malgr&eacute; ces temps de forte crise &eacute;conomique et financi&egrave;re, LCB Bank a pris l&rsquo;option d&rsquo;investir dans la formation et l&rsquo;&eacute;quipement de son capital humain, qu&rsquo;il place au centre du d&eacute;veloppement de ses activit&eacute;s, pour se pr&eacute;parer aussi &agrave; la reprise d&rsquo;activit&eacute;s, gr&acirc;ce &agrave; la relance de l&rsquo;&eacute;conomie dans les mois &agrave; venir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ceci constitue une dynamique de changement pour &laquo; aller plus loin, par rapport aux enjeux de l&rsquo;heure&hellip;&raquo;, selon l&rsquo;expression de M. Rachid RAISSI, Directeur G&eacute;n&eacute;ral Adjoint dans son allocution de circonstance &agrave; Pointe Noire en Juillet 2017.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dans cet environnement de forte concurrence et de forte crise financi&egrave;re, notre mani&egrave;re de servir et la qualit&eacute; des prestations que nous d&eacute;livrons sont des pr&eacute;occupations couvertes par les diff&eacute;rents modules, qui se d&eacute;roulent tout au long de ces dispositifs de formation, avec l&rsquo;espoir de voir progressivement nos habitudes et nos comportements chang&eacute;s positivement pour le bien de notre client&egrave;le.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&laquo;Bonguissa&raquo;, le programme qui a &eacute;t&eacute; lanc&eacute; sur l&rsquo;am&eacute;lioration des pratiques commerciales s&rsquo;inscrit dans la dynamique d&eacute;sormais en marche. Il s&rsquo;agit de donner &agrave;<strong>&nbsp;LCB Bank</strong>&nbsp;les moyens de ses ambitions, et &agrave; notre client&egrave;le les raisons de continuer &agrave; nous renouveler sa confiance &raquo;, expliquait M. Rachid RAISSI.</p>\r\n','<p>This program is part of a dynamic initiated by our bank aimed at transforming both material and human capital in the financial center of the Republic of Congo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This training followed, as we know, the very participatory approach, which involved the actors of the network of our bank&#39;s Branches, in a series of workshops which made it possible to draw up an inventory of our old commercial practices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This process revealed a number of findings, which formed the roadmap of the system for improving business practices, which the teams who took part in the various workshops called &quot;BONGUISSA&quot;.<br />\r\nOur common ambition through &quot;BONGUISSA&quot; has consisted in improving who we are, our way of doing, speaking, welcoming and serving our customers; This is why this training was preceded by the &quot;MBONGWANA&quot; program, launched in November 2016, as a support and capacity building mechanism for the managers of our bank.<br />\r\nAs an employee of LCB Bank, we are aware of the challenges of the day, and want to do better, change and continue to better serve our customers and retain them, but also to further consolidate our ties with them.<br />\r\nWhat we all want and which remains at the center of our concerns today is to give our customers the reasons to continue to renew their trust in us. A real challenge, it will be said! But we will do it with the same burst of determination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite these times of severe economic and financial crisis, LCB Bank has taken the option of investing in training and equipping its human capital, which it places at the center of the development of its activities, to also prepare for the resumption of activities, thanks to the recovery of the economy in the coming months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This constitutes a dynamic of change to &quot;go further, in relation to the challenges of the day ...&quot;, according to the expression of Mr. Rachid RAISSI, Deputy Managing Director in his speech for the occasion in Pointe Noire in July 2017.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this environment of strong competition and severe financial crisis, our way of serving and the quality of the services we deliver are concerns covered by the various modules, which take place throughout these training systems, with the hope of gradually see our habits and behaviors positively changed for the good of our customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Bonguissa&quot;, the program that was launched on improving business practices, is part of the momentum now underway. It is about giving LCB Bank the means to achieve its ambitions, and our customers the reasons to continue to renew their trust in us &quot;, explained Mr. Rachid RAISSI.</p>\r\n',1),(12,'bg-img5f6cc5d14d50a0zna160096404944430008.jpg','bg-img5f6cc5d1b23350anj160096404991221101.jpg','bg-img5f6cc5d21d0488yfj160096405082524801.jpg',1600964050,NULL,'dispositif-de-formation-mbongwana','mbongwana-training-device','Dispositif de formation MBONGWANA','MBONGWANA training device','Le capital humain de LCB Bank s’est engagé à investir dans la formation à travers le programme « Mbongwana » destiné aux managers de notre institution.','LCB Bank\'s human capital is committed to investing in training through the \"Mbongwana\" program for managers of our institution.','<p>Mbongwana est un parcours certifiant, qui b&eacute;n&eacute;ficie de l&rsquo;appui de la BMCE Bank of Africa Academy, partenaires privili&eacute; de ce programme, implant&eacute; &agrave; Casablanca au Maroc, dont l&rsquo;une des missions est d&rsquo;accompagner BMCE Bank of Africa, maison m&egrave;re de LCB Bank, dans la r&eacute;alisation de ses objectifs strat&eacute;giques, en offrant &agrave; son capital humain les moyens techniques, de d&eacute;veloppement personnel et manag&eacute;riaux ad&eacute;quats.</p>\r\n','<p>Mbongwana is a certifying course, which benefits from the support of the BMCE Bank of Africa Academy, privileged partners of this program, located in Casablanca in Morocco, one of the missions of which is to support BMCE Bank of Africa, parent company of LCB Bank, in achieving its strategic objectives, by offering its human capital adequate technical, personal and managerial development resources.</p>\r\n',1),(13,'bg-img5f6cc8b8d0d5e5ikt160096479245630097.jpg','bg-img5f6cc8b9455f92ing160096479332477403.jpg','bg-img5f6cc8b97afe37avy160096479329180067.jpg',1600964794,NULL,'activite-de-vulgarisation-des-valeurs-lcb-bank','lcb-bank-values-popularization-activities','Activités de Vulgarisation des valeurs LCB BANK','LCB BANK Values Popularization Activities','A l’issue de l’évaluation a mis parcours du dispositif (« Mbongawana » qui signifie « changement en langue locale») destiné aux managers de LCB Bank, les participants avaient émis l’idée de la mise en place d’une charte des valeurs qui devraient être incarné au quotidien par l’ensemble du personnel.','At the end of the evaluation, the system (\"Mbongawana\" which means \"change in local language\") intended for LCB Bank managers, the participants had put forward the idea of ​​setting up a charter of values ​​that should be embodied on a daily basis by all staff.','<p>Le comit&eacute; de projet mis en place dans le cadre de l&rsquo;&eacute;laboration de ladite charte a travaill&eacute; dans l&rsquo;objectif de proposer les diff&eacute;rentes d&eacute;clinaisons des (5) cinq valeurs (La bienveillance, l&rsquo;int&eacute;grit&eacute;, le respect, la performance et l&rsquo;innovation). Parmi les activit&eacute;s li&eacute;es &agrave; la strat&eacute;gie de vulgarisation de la chartre de valeurs LCB Bank se trouvent l&rsquo;organisation des ateliers des valeurs chaque vendredi matin. L&rsquo;atelier s&rsquo;appelle &laquo; le CAFE DU COIN &raquo;. Les participants au &laquo; CAFE DU COIN &raquo; sont des coll&egrave;gues provenant de plusieurs entit&eacute;s de la Banque.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dans la pratique, un animateur est choisi lors de la tenue de caque &laquo; CAFE DU COIN &raquo;, pour animer la s&eacute;ance qui dure g&eacute;n&eacute;ralement 30 minutes de 8heures &agrave; -8h 30. L&rsquo;animateur pr&eacute;sente les objectifs du caf&eacute; qui consistent &agrave; vulgariser la charte des valeurs LCB Bank.<br />\r\nLe caf&eacute; est servi en toute libert&eacute; dans une ambiance bon enfant et les &eacute;changent se d&eacute;roulent dans cette atmosph&egrave;re.<br />\r\nA chaque caf&eacute; du coin, les images des vid&eacute;os du caf&eacute; pr&eacute;c&eacute;dente sont projet&eacute;es. La tradition devrait permettre d&rsquo;organiser en visio-conf&eacute;rence chaque vendredi de fa&ccedil;on &agrave; mieux vulgariser les 5 valeurs de cette charte au sein des forces vives de LCB Bank.<br />\r\nLa tenue du caf&eacute; du coin, permet aux employ&eacute;s de se rapprocher davantage de discuter et de partager dans un esprit de v&eacute;rit&eacute; tout ce qui concerne la vie professionnelle, les d&eacute;fis, les difficult&eacute;s et les challenges v&eacute;cus au quotidien dans l&rsquo;exercice de leurs m&eacute;tiers.<br />\r\nA ce jour 7 &laquo; CAFE DU COIN ont &eacute;t&eacute; tenus &agrave; Brazzaville et une fois &agrave; Pointe Noire, la Direction G&eacute;n&eacute;rale de LCB Bank a eu le plaisir de participer &agrave; cette activit&eacute; de fa&ccedil;on &agrave; toucher du doigt la r&eacute;alit&eacute; et l&rsquo;ambiance qui y r&egrave;gne. Ces ateliers, de l&rsquo;avis de tous laissent entrevoir une mobilisation de l&rsquo;ensemble du personnel autour de ces 5 valeurs que nous voulons tous incarner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A travers l&rsquo;Animation de &laquo; &eacute;change de pratiques &raquo; sur la th&eacute;matique &laquo; <strong>Faire vivre les valeurs de LCB Bank &hellip; au plus pr&egrave;s des comportements. Car, les valeurs prennent tout leur sens si elles se traduisent en comportement au quotidien dans les pratiques professionnelles. Ce fut l&rsquo;axe central des &eacute;changes lors de la tenue de tous les &laquo;CAFE DU COIN</strong> &raquo;.</p>\r\n','<p>The project committee set up within the framework of the development of the said charter worked with the objective of proposing the different variations of the (5) five values ​​(Benevolence, integrity, respect, performance and innovation). Among the activities related to the popularization strategy of the LCB Bank values ​​charter are the organization of values ​​workshops every Friday morning. The workshop is called &quot;CAFE DU COIN&quot;. The participants in the &quot;COFFEE COIN&quot; are colleagues from several Bank entities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In practice, a facilitator is chosen during the &ldquo;COFFEE COIN&rdquo; caque, to animate the session which generally lasts 30 minutes from 8 am to -8.30 am The facilitator presents the objectives of the caf&eacute; which consist in popularizing the charter LCB Bank securities.<br />\r\nCoffee is served freely in a friendly atmosphere and the exchanges take place in this atmosphere.<br />\r\nAt each caf&eacute; in the area, images from videos from the previous caf&eacute; are shown. Tradition should make it possible to organize a videoconference every Friday so as to better popularize the 5 values ​​of this charter within LCB Bank&rsquo;s lifeblood.<br />\r\nHolding the local caf&eacute; allows employees to get closer to discussing and sharing in a spirit of truth all that concerns professional life, the challenges, difficulties and challenges experienced on a daily basis in the exercise of their jobs. .<br />\r\nTo date 7 &ldquo;CAFE DU COIN have been held in Brazzaville and once in Pointe Noire, the General Management of LCB Bank had the pleasure of participating in this activity so as to touch the reality and the atmosphere that reigns there. . These workshops, in the opinion of all, suggest a mobilization of all staff around these 5 values ​​that we all want to embody.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through the animation of &quot;exchange of practices&quot; on the theme &quot;<strong>Bringing LCB Bank&#39;s values ​​to life ... as close as possible to behavior. Because values ​​take on their full meaning if they translate into daily behavior in professional practices. This was the central axis of the discussions during all the &quot;COFFEE DU COIN&quot; events</strong>.&quot;</p>\r\n',1),(14,'bg-img5f6cca333b2c61wmf160096517193028059.jpg','bg-img5f6cca337ce393ixo160096517171678929.jpg','bg-img5f6cca33a30ac5ixw160096517133442216.jpg',1600965172,NULL,'lancement-du-credit-lcb-bank-achat-tv-startimes','launch-of-the-lcb-bank-loan-tv-startimes-purchase','Lancement du crédit LCB Bank achat TV Startimes','Launch of the LCB Bank loan for TV Startimes purchase','lcb bank','lcb bank','<p>lcb bank</p>\r\n','<p>lcb bank</p>\r\n',0),(15,'bg-img5f6ccaf9d39e68bqx160096536924728927.jpg','bg-img5f6ccaf9ea3e73ouk160096536983343931.jpg','bg-img5f6ccaf9f21626ngr160096536902122700.jpg',1600965370,NULL,'partenariat-lcb-bank-et-mastercard','lcb-bank-and-mastercard-partnership','Partenariat LCB Bank et MasterCard','LCB Bank and MasterCard partnership','LCB Bank, filiale du Groupe BMCE Bank of Africa, a signé avec Mastercard le 14 octobre 2017 leur parte¬nariat axé sur la digitalisation de son offre bancaire en République du Congo. L’accord de partenariat signé permettra d’enrichir notre offre sur les moyens de paie¬ments, encourageant ainsi l’utilisation de nouvelles solutions digitales qui favoriseront l’innovation dans le secteur bancaire.','LCB Bank, a subsidiary of the BMCE Bank of Africa Group, signed their partnership with Mastercard on October 14, 2017, focused on the digitization of its banking offer in the Republic of Congo. The signed partnership agreement will enrich our offer on payment methods, thus encouraging the use of new digital solutions that will promote innovation in the banking sector.','<p>La digitalisation de nos moyens de paiements permet&not;tra &agrave; tous les citoyens d&rsquo;avoir acc&egrave;s &agrave; un choix plus large de solutions de paiement pratiques, s&ucirc;res et faciles d&rsquo;utilisation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les cartes Mastercard sont dot&eacute;es de puces r&eacute;pon&not;dant &agrave; la norme EMV, y compris les cr&eacute;dits et d&eacute;bits pr&eacute;pay&eacute;s, et, suivies de solutions telles que Master&not;pass QR. &laquo;LCB Bank et Mastercard, s&rsquo;engagent &agrave; offrir l&rsquo;acc&egrave;s &agrave; des services financiers abordables &agrave; tous les clients. Gr&acirc;ce &agrave; notre partenariat, LCB Bank dispose d&eacute;sormais de la possibilit&eacute; de four&not;nir une large gamme de produits et de services Mastercard, ce qui permettra aux nationaux et aux &eacute;trangers de payer plus facilement et de fa&ccedil;on pratique les biens et services &raquo;, a d&eacute;clar&eacute; Mohamed TAHRI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le d&eacute;veloppement d&rsquo;une &eacute;conomie plus int&eacute;gr&eacute;e &eacute;tant l&rsquo;un des objectifs des pays en mati&egrave;re de d&eacute;veloppe&not;ment, l&rsquo;acc&egrave;s via la digitalisation aux services finan&not;ciers efficaces au niveau local deviendra une r&eacute;alit&eacute; pour tous les citoyens, associ&eacute; &agrave; une forte acceptation dans notre pays mais aussi dans le monde entier. LCB Bank et Mastercard s&rsquo;engagent aussi dans une nouvelle &egrave;re de transformation digitale de l&rsquo;offre ban&not;caire congolaise, qui va assur&eacute;ment avoir un impact positif sur l&rsquo;augmentation du taux de bancarisation des populations &agrave; ce jour exclues du syst&egrave;me bancaire. &laquo;La relation LCB Bank-Mastercard fait partie de notre engagement &agrave; renforcer financi&egrave;rement 100 millions de personnes en Afrique d&rsquo;ici 2020 et aidera &agrave; garantir notre capacit&eacute; &agrave; offrir aux clients un soutien continu dans tout le pays&raquo;, a expliqu&eacute; Mohamed Elbelamachi, Directeur R&eacute;gional Afrique subsaharienne francophone de Mastercard. Concluant ses propos lors de la signature de ce par&not;tenariat, Monsieur Elbelamachi a ajout&eacute; que : &laquo;Nous sommes heureux de faire partie de ce voyage de transformation en R&eacute;publique du Congo&raquo;.</p>\r\n','<p>The digitization of our means of payment will allow all citizens to have access to a wider choice of practical, secure and easy-to-use payment solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mastercard cards have chips that meet the EMV standard, including prepaid credits and debits, and, followed by solutions such as Masterpass QR. &ldquo;LCB Bank and Mastercard are committed to providing access to affordable financial services to all customers. Thanks to our partnership, LCB Bank now has the possibility of providing a wide range of Mastercard products and services, which will make it easier and more convenient for nationals and foreigners to pay for goods and services, &rdquo;said Mohamed TAHRI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the development of a more integrated economy is one of the countries&#39; development objectives, access through digitization to efficient financial services at the local level will become a reality for all citizens, associated with a strong acceptance in our country but also in the whole world. LCB Bank and Mastercard are also embarking on a new era of digital transformation of the Congolese banking offer, which will undoubtedly have a positive impact on the increase in the banking rate of populations currently excluded from the banking system. &ldquo;The LCB Bank-Mastercard relationship is part of our commitment to financially strengthen 100 million people in Africa by 2020 and will help ensure our ability to provide customers with continued support across the country,&rdquo; explained Mohamed Elbelamachi, Director Mastercard French-speaking Sub-Saharan Africa regional. Concluding his remarks during the signing of this partnership, Mr. Elbelamachi added that: &quot;We are happy to be part of this transformational journey in the Republic of Congo&quot;.</p>\r\n',1),(16,'bg-img5f6cccbcab03f0tcg160096582042080201.jpg','bg-img5f6cccbce87910yyh160096582070104899.jpg','bg-img5f6cccbd19daa9zps160096582128844330.jpg',1600965821,NULL,'renovation-du-centre-d-affaire-brazzaville-et-de-l-agence-cabral','renovation-of-brazzaville-bussiness-center-and-cabral-agency','Rénovation du Centre D’Affaire Brazzaville et de l’Agence Cabral','Renovation of the Brazzaville Business Center and Cabral Agency','Pour un accueil convivial de notre clientèle entreprise et dans le cadre du vaste chantier de rénovation de notre réseau d’agences, nous venions de nous doter d’un Centre d’Affaires pour les entreprises. Un ouvrage qui rentre dans le cadre de la stratégie globale de LCB Bank axée sur l’optimisation du maillage territorial du réseau LCB Bank à travers une spécialisation de nos différentes agences réservées aux particuliers, professionnels ainsi que les petites et les grandes entreprises (PME/PMI), car, nous sommes déterminés et engagés vers une meilleure prise en charge et un meilleur accompagnement de nos partenaires.','For a friendly welcome to our corporate customers and as part of the vast renovation project of our branch network, we had just set up a Business Center for companies. A book that falls within the framework of LCB Bank\'s overall strategy focused on optimizing the territorial coverage of the LCB Bank network through a specialization of our various branches reserved for individuals, professionals as well as small and large companies (SMEs / PMI), because we are determined and committed to better support and better support for our partners.','<p>L&rsquo;ouverture de ce Centre d&rsquo;Affaires de Brazzaville est intervenue aussi sur le m&ecirc;me site du Si&egrave;ge social de LCB Bank, apr&egrave;s celle&nbsp;<strong>de l&rsquo;Agence Elite</strong>&nbsp;r&eacute;serv&eacute;e pour servir notre client&egrave;le Elite et celle de&nbsp;<strong>l&rsquo;Agence Cabral pour une prise en charge de notre client&egrave;le, des particuliers et des professionnels</strong>. Avec ce pr&eacute;cieux ouvrage compos&eacute; d&rsquo;espaces de caisses, de bureaux des Charg&eacute;s d&rsquo;Affaires et de Charg&eacute;s de Comptes, de bureaux de Responsables du centre d&rsquo;Affaires et naturellement d&rsquo;un hall d&rsquo;attente, l&rsquo;engagement port&eacute; par les instances de gouvernance de LCB Bank, d&rsquo;allier une relation de proximit&eacute; et une meilleure prise en charge de notre client&egrave;le entreprise devient une r&eacute;alit&eacute; mat&eacute;rialis&eacute;e &agrave; travers le Centre d&rsquo;Affaires qui renforce aujourd&rsquo;hui notre fiert&eacute; !</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En effet, au-del&agrave; du contexte &eacute;conomique et financier difficile de l&rsquo;heure et en attendant la relance prochaine de l&rsquo;&eacute;conomie nationale, notre banque est non seulement d&eacute;termin&eacute;e mais surtout continue &agrave; investir suffisamment dans la logistique et son personnel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Notre objectif principal, c&rsquo;est notre action au service de la client&egrave;le en maintenant toujours un service de meilleure qualit&eacute; possible, pour consolider le contrat de confiance que nous avions &eacute;tabli avec notre client&egrave;le.</p>\r\n','<p>The opening of this Brazzaville Business Center also took place on the same site of LCB Bank&#39;s Headquarters, after that of the Elite Agency reserved to serve our Elite customers and that of the Cabral Agency for support. of our customers, individuals and professionals. With this precious structure made up of checkout areas, offices for account managers and account managers, offices for managers of the business center and naturally a waiting hall, the commitment made by the authorities of governance of LCB Bank, to combine a close relationship and better support for our corporate customers becomes a reality materialized through the Business Center which today reinforces our pride!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Indeed, beyond the difficult economic and financial context of the hour and pending the imminent revival of the national economy, our bank is not only determined but above all continues to invest sufficiently in logistics and its staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our main objective is our action in customer service by always maintaining the best possible quality service, to consolidate the contract of trust that we had established with our customers.</p>\r\n',1),(17,'bg-img5f6dc6c1db17f1aju160102982542029895.jpg','bg-img5f6dc6c229b097afo160102982639169622.jpg','bg-img5f6dc6c2596d89qxm160102982693426588.jpg',1601029826,NULL,'lcb-bank-poursuit-son-engagement-en-tant-que-acteur-social','lcb-bank-continues-its-commitment-as-a-social-player','LCB Bank poursuit son engagement en tant que acteur social','LCB Bank continues its commitment as a social player','L’Unité des Soins Intensifs Cardiologiques (USIC) du CHU de Brazzaville a été inaugurée le lundi 14 aout 2017 en même temps que la visite de l’unité d’assainissement et la réception du matériel relatif à l’Opération d’assainissement du Centre Hospitalier de Brazzaville dénommée « pas de Santé sans Propreté » en présence de Madame la Ministre de la Santé et de la population Jacqueline Lydia Mikolo','The Cardiological Intensive Care Unit (ICU) of the Brazzaville University Hospital was inaugurated on Monday August 14, 2017 at the same time as the visit of the sanitation unit and the reception of the material relating to the Center sanitation operation. Hospitalier de Brazzaville called \"no Health without Cleanliness\" in the presence of the Minister of Health and the population Jacqueline Lydia Mikolo','<p>LCB Bank y a &eacute;t&eacute; invit&eacute;e en tant que partenaire financier actif lors de ces deux &eacute;v&egrave;nements au cours desquels, LCB Bank a re&ccedil;u non seulement les chaleureux remerciements de Madame la Ministre de la Sant&eacute; et de la population mais surtout des encouragements &agrave; progresser et &agrave; maintenir cet &eacute;lan de banque citoyenne et d&rsquo;acteur social.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sied de souligner que ces appuis de LCB Bank traduisent sa volont&eacute; de mat&eacute;rialiser permanemment son caract&egrave;re social. LCB Bank inscrit son action dans la soci&eacute;t&eacute; congolaise et dans son environnement &eacute;conomique dans la dur&eacute;e, affichant son ambition de continuer &agrave; &ecirc;tre un partenaire strat&eacute;gique du financement de l&rsquo;&eacute;conomie congolaise.<br />\r\nDepuis 2016 LCB Bank, &agrave; travers sa fondation a marqu&eacute; l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e par plusieurs actions t&eacute;moignant de son engagement social. C&rsquo;est dans ce cadre que LCB Bank a apport&eacute; sa contribution financi&egrave;re aux actions men&eacute;es &agrave; l&rsquo;initiative de la Fondation Calissa IKAMA, dont la vocation est de lutter contre le cancer de l&rsquo;enfant.<br />\r\nCet &eacute;lan de c&oelig;ur et son engagement social ont valu &agrave; la banque, la reconnaissance des instances de la Fondation Calissa IKAMA, en lui d&eacute;cernant un titre honorifique.<br />\r\nL&rsquo;&eacute;v&egrave;nement avait eu lieu au si&egrave;ge social de la banque, le vendredi 03 mars 2017. La d&eacute;l&eacute;gation de la Fondation &eacute;tait conduite par Mme Olga Euphrasie AKYLANGONGO.<br />\r\nCette c&eacute;r&eacute;monie a connu, outre la remise du titre honorifique &agrave; LCB Bank, le port du ruban d&rsquo;or, symbole de la lutte contre le cancer de l&rsquo;enfant, la signature du livre d&rsquo;or de la Fondation, avant de terminer par une photo de famille.<br />\r\nCette action de bienfaisance n&rsquo;est pas isol&eacute;e, puisque LCB Bank a aussi orient&eacute; son action en direction d&rsquo;un orphelinat &laquo; Mwana village &raquo; &agrave; Pointe-Noire. C&rsquo;&eacute;tait pr&eacute;cis&eacute;ment le 08 mars 2017, journ&eacute;e internationale des droits de la femme, &agrave; l&rsquo;occasion de laquelle des repr&eacute;sentantes des femmes de LCB Bank ont men&eacute; une action consistant &agrave; apporter un don de vivres en faveur des enfants de cette maison d&rsquo;accueil. LCB Bank est d&eacute;termin&eacute;e &agrave; assumer sa responsabilit&eacute; d&rsquo;entreprise citoyenne, &agrave; travers un engagement sur le terrain des r&eacute;alit&eacute;s soci&eacute;tales impliquant l&rsquo;humain. Assur&eacute;ment LCB Bank est aussi un acteur impliqu&eacute; dans la r&eacute;ponse aux probl&egrave;mes de son environnement social. C&rsquo;est aussi cela faire de la banque autrement avec un regard bienveillant sur la soci&eacute;t&eacute;.</p>\r\n','<p>LCB Bank was invited as an active financial partner during these two events during which LCB Bank received not only the warm thanks from the Minister of Health and the population but above all encouragement to progress and maintain this momentum of citizen banking and social actor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It should be noted that this support from LCB Bank reflects its desire to permanently materialize its social character. LCB Bank is committed to Congolese society and its economic environment over time, showing its ambition to continue to be a strategic partner in the financing of the Congolese economy.<br />\r\nSince 2016 LCB Bank, through its foundation, has marked the year with several actions demonstrating its social commitment. It is within this framework that LCB Bank has made its financial contribution to actions carried out at the initiative of the Calissa IKAMA Foundation, whose vocation is to fight against childhood cancer.<br />\r\nThis enthusiasm and its social commitment have earned the bank the recognition of the authorities of the Calissa IKAMA Foundation, by awarding it an honorary title.<br />\r\nThe event took place at the bank&#39;s head office on Friday March 03, 2017. The Foundation delegation was led by Ms. Olga Euphrasie AKYLANGONGO.<br />\r\nThis ceremony saw, in addition to the presentation of the honorary title to LCB Bank, the wearing of the gold ribbon, symbol of the fight against childhood cancer, the signing of the Foundation&#39;s guestbook, before ending with a family photo.<br />\r\nThis charitable action is not isolated, since LCB Bank has also directed its action towards a &quot;Mwana village&quot; orphanage in Pointe-Noire. It was precisely March 8, 2017, international women&#39;s rights day, on the occasion of which representatives of women from LCB Bank led an action consisting in providing a donation of food for the children of this house of Home. LCB Bank is determined to assume its responsibility as a corporate citizen, through an engagement on the ground of societal realities involving people. Certainly LCB Bank is also an actor involved in responding to the problems of its social environment. It is also about doing banking differently with a benevolent outlook on society.</p>\r\n',1),(18,'bg-img5f6dc8f5b5bdc4bme160103038993881697.jpg','bg-img5f6dc8f5da5f79buy160103038928445619.jpg','bg-img5f6dc8f5ef2b67kla160103038993667437.jpg',1601030390,1601031010,'lancement-bancassurance','bancassurance-launch','Lancement Bancassurance','Bancassurance launch','Dans la perspective d’élargir sa gamme de produits sur le marché bancaire au Congo, LCB Bank a procédé au lancement des produits BANCASSURANCE à Brazzaville le lundi 07 octobre 2019 à l’hôtel Radisson Blu et à Pointe Noire le mercredi 10 octobre 2019 à l’hôtel ELAIS.','With a view to expanding its range of products on the banking market in Congo, LCB Bank launched the BANCASSURANCE products in Brazzaville on Monday 07 October 2019 at the Radisson Blu hotel and in Pointe Noire on Wednesday 10 October 2019 at the ELAIS hotel.','<p>Dans cet environnement de forte concurrence LCB Bank a &eacute;largi sa gamme de produits pour fid&eacute;liser sa client&egrave;le et accro&icirc;tre sa part de march&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les produits bancassurance que LCB Bank offre &agrave; son aimable client&egrave;le pour garantir un avenir meilleur&nbsp;sont les suivants&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Assurance Automobile&nbsp;:&nbsp;</strong>permet de vous mettre &agrave; l&rsquo;abri des accidents, vous pouvez maintenant payer votre &agrave; cr&eacute;dit, par virement ou en esp&egrave;ces dans toutes les agences LCB Bank&nbsp;;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Assurance</strong>&nbsp;<strong>ELIKIA Scolaire&nbsp;:</strong>&nbsp;vous garantit une prise en charge des frais de scolarit&eacute; de vos enfants en cas de sinistre (D&eacute;c&egrave;s ou invalidit&eacute; d&eacute;finitive et absolue)&nbsp;;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Assurance</strong>&nbsp;<strong>LIKAMA&nbsp;:&nbsp;</strong>garantit le paiement d&rsquo;un capital en de d&eacute;c&egrave;s, toute cause d&rsquo;invalidit&eacute; absolue ou d&eacute;finitive, ainsi que des frais fun&eacute;raires en cas de d&eacute;c&egrave;s d&rsquo;un membre de votre famille nucl&eacute;aire&nbsp;;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Assurance</strong>&nbsp;<strong>EMPRUNTEUR&nbsp;:</strong>&nbsp;le paiement de l&rsquo;encours de votre pr&ecirc;t est garanti en cas de sinistre.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>In this environment of strong competition LCB Bank has broadened its range of products to build customer loyalty and increase its market share.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The bancassurance products that LCB Bank offers to its friendly customers to guarantee a better future are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Automobile Insurance</strong>: allows you to protect yourself from accidents, you can now pay your credit, by transfer or in cash at any LCB Bank branch;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>ELIKIA School Insurance</strong>: guarantees coverage of your children&#39;s school fees in the event of a claim (death or permanent and absolute disability);</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>LIKAMA insurance</strong>: guarantees the payment of a capital on death, any cause of absolute or definitive disability, as well as funeral costs in the event of the death of a member of your nuclear family;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>BORROWER insurance</strong>: payment of your outstanding loan is guaranteed in the event of a claim.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1),(19,'bg-img5f6dcd67a184a2vuf160103152772301969.jpg','bg-img5f6dcd67c1f396lwo160103152799463841.jpg','bg-img5f6dcd67d00843dpd160103152714434954.jpg',1601031528,1604063876,'lancement-de-la-banque-digitale','launch-of-digital-bank','Lancement de la Banque Digitale','Launch of Digital Bank','Le Directeur général de LCB Bank, Mohamed Essaid BENJELLOUN TOUIMI a indiqué le 9 février 2019 que son institution emboîtait le pas dans la révolution digitale en constituant un grand saut vers l’innovation dans le secteur financier et bancaire de la place.\r\n','The Managing Director of LCB Bank, Mohamed Essaid BENJELLOUN TOUIMI said on February 9, 2019 that his institution was following suit in the digital revolution by constituting a big leap towards innovation in the financial and banking sector of the place.','<p>&quot;Avec LCB Cash, le transfert d&rsquo;argent au niveau national est disponible &agrave; moindre frais et disponible dans toutes les agences du plus grand r&eacute;seau bancaire de la place, celui de LCB Bank et chez les partenaires via l&rsquo;utilisation de votre t&eacute;l&eacute;phone, votre tablette&quot;, a fait savoir Mohamed Essaid BENJELLOUN TOUIMI, lors de la c&eacute;r&eacute;monie de lancement de la banque digitale LCB Cash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pour profiter des services de LCB Cash, il suffit de t&eacute;l&eacute;charger l&rsquo;application LCB Pay, disponible sur Google Play et App Store. LCB Bank permet &agrave; tous, d&rsquo;avoir un compte via LCB Cash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&laquo; Toutes les transactions faites via LCB Cash sont directement reli&eacute;es &agrave; LCB Bank. Vous pouvez faire le d&eacute;p&ocirc;t d&rsquo;argent dans les agences LCB Bank ou chez nos partenaires, vous allez envoyer de l&rsquo;argent &agrave; partir de votre t&eacute;l&eacute;phone sans vous d&eacute;placer, vous allez payer vos courses &raquo;, a ajout&eacute; l&rsquo;Administrateur Directeur g&eacute;n&eacute;ral de LBC Bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le Directeur de la Banque Digitale, Guy No&euml;l BAMBI-BONE, quant &agrave; lui, est intervenu pour faire connaitre davantage les services de cette structure qui devient encore plus proche de ses clients &agrave; moindre co&ucirc;t.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La Banque Digitale simplifie les d&eacute;marches en donnant aux clients la possibilit&eacute; d&rsquo;ouvrir un compte bancaire en ligne et acc&eacute;der &agrave; plusieurs de ses services. Elle permet aussi aux clients d&rsquo;effectuer la majorit&eacute; de leurs op&eacute;rations bancaires, sans se d&eacute;placer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La Banque digitale lanc&eacute;e n&rsquo;est que la d&eacute;monstration du dynamisme de LCB Bank &agrave; satisfaire davantage sa client&egrave;le face &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;mergence de la finance digitale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCB Bank rassure ses clients sur la qualit&eacute; des services. Ce projet, qui a pris 2 ans pour aboutir, permet aux clients de changer le comportement dans les op&eacute;rations bancaires.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCB Bank est une filiale de la BMCE Bank of Africa, une des banques leader du Royaume du Maroc. LCB Bank d&eacute;tient aujourd&rsquo;hui le r&eacute;seau d&rsquo;agences bancaires le plus large de la R&eacute;publique du Congo, avec une vingtaine d&rsquo;agences implant&eacute;es &agrave; Brazzaville, Pointe-Noire, Dolisie, Nkayi, Ouesso, Gombe et Oyo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avec LCB Pay :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Payez vos courses ;</li>\r\n	<li>Envoyez et recevez de l&rsquo;argent ;</li>\r\n	<li>Rechargez votre compte ;</li>\r\n	<li>Consultez votre relev&eacute; et votre solde ;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>JOKERPASS :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Payer &ndash; cumuler des points.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>&quot;With LCB Cash, money transfer at the national level is available at a lower cost and available in all the branches of the largest banking network in the area, that of LCB Bank and at partners via the use of your phone, your tablet&quot; , said Mohamed Essaid BENJELLOUN TOUIMI, during the launch ceremony of the LCB Cash digital bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To take advantage of LCB Cash services, simply download the LCB Pay application, available on Google Play and App Store. LCB Bank allows everyone to have an account via LCB Cash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;All transactions made via LCB Cash are directly linked to LCB Bank. You can deposit money at LCB Bank branches or at our partners, you will send money from your phone without moving, you will pay for your groceries &rdquo;, added the Managing Director of LBC Bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Director of the Digital Bank, Guy No&euml;l BAMBI-BONE, meanwhile, intervened to increase awareness of the services of this structure which is becoming even closer to its customers at lower cost.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The digital bank&nbsp;simplifies the procedures by giving customers the possibility of opening an online bank account and accessing several of its services. It also allows customers to do the majority of their banking transactions without having to travel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The digital bank launched is only the demonstration of LCB Bank&#39;s dynamism to better satisfy its customers in the face of the emergence of digital finance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCB Bank reassures its customers about the quality of services. This project, which took 2 years to complete, enables customers to change behavior in banking operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCB Bank is a subsidiary of BMCE Bank of Africa, one of the leading banks in the Kingdom of Morocco. LCB Bank now owns the largest branch network in the Republic of Congo, with around 20 branches located in Brazzaville, Pointe-Noire, Dolisie, Nkayi, Ouesso, Gombe and Oyo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With LCB Pay:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pay for your shopping;</li>\r\n	<li>Send and receive money;</li>\r\n	<li>Top up your account;</li>\r\n	<li>Consult your statement and your balance;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>JOKERPASS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pay - collect points.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1);
